Title: City League Finals
Description:
Steve Colburn, Tournament Director. 
The Pandanet-AGA City League has been run for the last two years with players from all over the US and Canada. They have formed teams around cities and played on IGS to see who is the strongest city. This tournament has players from 1p to 13k within the three leagues. Full tournament information, players, and game records can be found on the Pandanet City League website. http://pandanet-igs.com/communities/agacityleague.html

Facebook Open Go Simul
Description: Artificial Intelligence has taken go into new realms and this year at the US Go Congress attendees will be able to learn and improve their own games and have a lot of fun interacting with an AI. This Simul is a no-handicap teaching game with Facebook's OpenGo. OpenGo features a 20-0 record against top-30 professionals. Each player will be mailed an SGF file after the game along with annotations from OpenGo.

Running your first Tournament, Chris Kirschner, Terry Benson
Description:
DAY 1: Running Your First Tournament - The Basics (Chris)

This session will cover all the basics of running a tournament, including…
• Planning: Time limits, rounds, type of pairing, rules, membership requirements, entry fee, prizes, tie break system
• Publicity: E-Journal, AGA Event Calendar
• Registration
• Pairing: Swiss, Swiss McMahon, round robin, knockouts
• Reporting: AGA ratings database, E-Journal

DAY 1: Running Your First Tournament - Rules (Terry)

This session will cover rules in more depth.
